title State Machine - servicemanagerproxy/ServiceEnvironment
skinparam state {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
}
left to right direction
hide empty description
state "Observe" as observe
state "EvaluateReady" as evaluate_ready
state "Ready" as ready
state "Retryable" as retryable
state "Failed" as failed
observe : read spec, tracked status, delete intent,\nand current OCI lifecycle
state "ResolveByLookup" as resolve_by_lookup
state "RejectUnsupportedDrift" as reject_unsupported_drift
[*] --> observe : reconcile
observe --> resolve_by_lookup : tracked identity missing
resolve_by_lookup --> evaluate_ready : lookup or create reaches\nACTIVE, SOFT_TERMINATED,\nCANCELED, TERMINATED (+6\nmore)
resolve_by_lookup --> retryable : OCI state in INITIALIZED,\nBEGIN_ACTIVATION,\nBEGIN_SOFT_TERMINATION,\nBEGIN_TERMINATION (+10 more)
resolve_by_lookup --> failed : unresolved OCI error or non-success state
observe --> evaluate_ready : OCI state in ACTIVE,\nSOFT_TERMINATED, CANCELED,\nTERMINATED (+6 more)
observe --> retryable : OCI state in INITIALIZED,\nBEGIN_ACTIVATION,\nBEGIN_SOFT_TERMINATION,\nBEGIN_TERMINATION (+10 more)
observe --> failed : unresolved OCI error or non-success state
evaluate_ready --> reject_unsupported_drift : force-new or conflicting\ndrift detected
reject_unsupported_drift --> ready : wait for spec or live state change
evaluate_ready --> ready : no supported drift remains
ready --> ready : no supported drift remains
retryable --> retryable : OCI remains retryable
failed --> failed : OCI remains terminal
note right of ready
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-controller-state-machine.svg
Start from the shared controller phase model and
specialize imported provider states, delete
targets, and failure exits here.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers map provider states into the shared
controller phases with explicit finalizer and
requeue policies.
service: servicemanagerproxy
slug: serviceenvironment
kind: ServiceEnvironment
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required / none
requeue: provisioning, updating
provider states: create INITIALIZED,
BEGIN_ACTIVATION; update BEGIN_SOFT_TERMINATION,
BEGIN_TERMINATION, BEGIN_DISABLING,
BEGIN_ENABLING (+8 more); delete none
supported drift: none
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartment_id, service_environment_id
create-only fields: none
list lookup:
oci_service_manager_proxy_service_environments
filters compartment_id, service_environment_id
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
Service Manager Proxy exposes
GetServiceEnvironment and
ListServiceEnvironments only in the pinned SDK,
so the published runtime is bind-existing and
observe-only.
Bind identity is explicit: reconcile requires
compartmentId and serviceEnvironmentId, tracks
the returned Service Manager identifier in
status, and uses ListServiceEnvironments only to
confirm absence after a reread no longer finds
the tracked environment.
No OCI create, update, or delete operation is
published. The controller treats
serviceEnvironmentId and compartmentId as
bind-only identity and performs Kubernetes-local
finalizer cleanup on delete.
Entitlement transitions beginning with BEGIN_
requeue, stable entitlement states settle
success, and FAILED_* plus TRA_UNKNOWN remain
terminal failures.
end note
@enduml
